{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5617b38d-4e63-4e48-be98-49e55c39cf21","content":"No repo context here, so here's the general guidance:\n\n### Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n**1. Update your test projects** — add to each `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n```\n\n**2. Replace the pipeline task.** Swap `VSTest@3` for `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script):\n\n```yaml\n# Before\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testSelector: 'testAssemblies'\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Build.ArtifactStagingDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=TestResults.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Build.ArtifactStagingDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n**3. Publish results & coverage:**\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '**/*.trx'\n    searchFolder: $(Build.ArtifactStagingDirectory)/TestResults\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Build.ArtifactStagingDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | vstest.console.exe | Tests are self-contained executables |\n| Invocation | `VSTest@3` task on DLLs | `dotnet test` on projects |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--logger trx` flag |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n\n> **Tip:** If you use Coverlet instead of the built-in collector, replace `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` with `--collect:\"XPlat Code Coverage\"` and ensure the `coverlet.collector` NuGet package is referenced.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"673ae4ba-fd6f-42fe-892b-8dc1db6b2ebf","outputTokens":634,"requestId":"4C18:7C3A8:D7817F:10B8902:6A01299E"},"id":"4af7f0e6-994e-4e2f-b4e8-7c543d214e5f","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:58:18.650Z","parentId":"ebaaf87d-55a6-405e-9143-97025537e6df"}
